type() is a built in function in python to which is used to tell us the type of the variable.

integer_type = 0
float_type = 0.0
bool_type = False
string_type = ""
list_type = []

print(type(integer_type))
print(type(float_type))
print(type(bool_type))
print(type(string_type))
print(type(list_type))

output:
<class 'int'>
<class 'float'>
<class 'bool'>
<class 'str'>
<class 'list'>
